 is a great money-saver because you make the pasta and ricotta from scratch.","Roll out small amounts of pasta dough at a time and cover remaining dough with a damp kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out.","For best results after rolling and cutting pasta, allow to dry 1-2 hours on a lightly floured kitchen towel.","After washing and drying the mixing bowl in step 3, you may wish to proceed with step 5 and the preparation of your fillings while the pasta dough rests. <br>","If you have a second Thermomix bowl, it will come in very handy in step 7, as you can insert the simmering basket into it and allow the ricotta to drain. <br>","To increase quantity, add 1 extra egg per additional 100 g flour. The maximum quantity at any one time is 500 g flour and 5 eggs. Increase kneading time to 3 minutes."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","2h","4 portions"]}